	abstract = {The just-in-time adaptive intervention ({JITAI}) is an intervention design aiming to provide the right type/amount of support, at the right time, by adapting to an individual’s changing internal and contextual state. The availability of increasingly powerful mobile and sensing technologies underpins the use of {JITAIs} to support health behavior, as in such a setting an individual’s state can change rapidly, unexpectedly, and in his/her natural environment.},
