	abstract = {Clinical Impact Statement Question: Can an online training tool be developed to include active rehearsal of cognitive behavioral techniques for psychosis with automated feedback that is comparable to ratings obtained by trained human raters? Findings: Our development and validation process demonstrated acceptable ratings of authenticity for simulated clients, high interrater reliability associated with a range of responses to the simulated client prompts, and high agreement between machine and human ratings. Meaning: Automated feedback of speciﬁc {CBT} skills can be provided by machine learning models, enabling the possibility of large-scale automated skills-based training. Next Steps: Future research should explore the acceptability and impact of psychotherapy performance-based learning powered by machine learning technology.},
